<p>To start you need to understand what it is, I suggest reading the docs I reference above.</p>
<p>Here you want to tune your motors voltage to produce the output of velocity that you want. So the first thing that you need to do is get velocity from your motor.</p>
<p>I can see your getSpeeds method is returning a blank MecanumWheelSpeeds. You can get the speed of your motors by using an Encoder. I see you have a brushless Sparkmax, so if you’re using Neo motors they have a Hall-effect internal encoder built in, you should be able to call it using neo.getEncoder()</p>
<p>The encoder should have a getRate method, this will return the change in your encoders rotations, it should be in rotation/second, so you will need to convert it into Meters per second.</p>
<p>From there you should create Feedforward and PIDControllers for each motor, and follow WPILibs <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> tuning a fly wheel for the steps on that.</p>
